<!DOCTYPE html>    ## [ doctype is a standard type which tells the language in which the webpage is written i.e html .(different standards = example : htmm 5 , xhtml etc) ]
<html>           ##[ tag in which  all code is nested between <html> and <\html> ]
<head>           ## [ tag  in which all the display code is to be written ]

    <title> My First Web Page </title>                                             ##[ display of title in the load bar ]
    <meta name="description" content="Page Description Here"/>                     ##[  meta  tag which describes the description provided with the link ]
    <meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html"; charset="utf-8"/>         ##[ utf-8 is a stype of character set used to write and display the content of the webpage  ] 
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1"/>          ##[  viewport sets the webpage according to device in which web is opened and content with
                                                                                          initial - scale = 1 is used to zome in zome outcontent displayed in webpage    ]

    <style type="text/css">             ##[ style tag is used to set rules of CSS = CASCADING STYLE SHEETS ( HOW IS THE WRITTEN TEXT IS TO BE DISPLAYED) ]
        Body {    
            color: red;
        }

    </style>

    <script>                             ##[ USED JAVA SCRPIT ALL OVER TO USE FUNCTION SET (IGNORE)]
        function myFunction() {
            var x = document.getElementById("fname");
            x.value = x.value.toUpperCase();
        }
    </script>
</head>

<body>
This is a Sample HTML Document.
This Javascript function will capitalize my name:
Enter your name: <input type="text" id="fname" onchange="myFunction()">     ##[  HOW TO CALL THE FUNCTION THAT IS TO BE DISPLAYED AS A CONTENT ON TOP LEFT OF WEB PAGE ]
</body>

</html> 
_________________________________________________________________________
##[] = TO BE REMOVED WHILE CREATING OF WEB PAGE , WRITTEN TO UNDERSTAND TAGS USED IN CREATING THE WEB CODE .
